/wiki/Blake_Smith: Blake Smith (born January 17, 1991) is an American soccer player who plays for USL Championship side San Antonio FC.
/wiki/New_Mexico_Lobos_men%27s_soccer: The New Mexico Lobos men's soccer team represented the University of New Mexico in all NCAA Division I men's soccer competitions from 1983 until 2018. The team became a soccer-only member of Conference USA in July 2013 after leaving the Mountain Pacific Sports Federation (the school's primary conference, the Mountain West, only sponsors that sport for women). The team is being cut after the 2019 season.
/wiki/2013_MLS_SuperDraft: The 2013 MLS SuperDraft was the fourteenth SuperDraft presented by Major League Soccer. The draft took place on January 17, 2013 in Indianapolis, Indiana at the Indiana Convention Center.
/wiki/Wandrille_Lef%C3%A8vre: Wandrille Lefèvre (born December 17, 1989) is a Canadian soccer player who plays as a centre back for AS Blainville.
/wiki/Montreal_Impact_Academy: Montreal Impact Academy (French: L'Academie De L'Impact De Montreal) is a Canadian professional soccer team based in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. Founded in 2010, their U-23 team is currently playing in the USL Premier Development League. They serve as the Academy to their parent club Montreal Impact.
/wiki/Maxim_Tissot: Maxim Tissot (born April 13, 1992) is a Canadian professional soccer player who most recently played for Ottawa Fury FC in the United Soccer League.
/wiki/Maxime_Cr%C3%A9peau: Maxime Crépeau (born April 11, 1994) is a Canadian soccer player who currently plays for Vancouver Whitecaps FC, as a goalkeeper.
/wiki/Zakaria_Messoudi: Zakaria Messoudi (born October 30, 1993) is a Canadian professional soccer player who plays as a midfielder.
/wiki/Paolo_DelPiccolo: Paolo DelPiccolo (born May 28, 1991) is an American soccer player who plays as a midfielder for Louisville City FC in the United Soccer League. He is also the club's current captain.
/wiki/Eintracht_Frankfurt: Eintracht Frankfurt e.V. (German pronunciation: [ˈʔaɪntʁaxt ˈfʁaŋkfʊʁt]) is a German professional sports club based in Frankfurt, Hesse, that is best known for its football club, currently playing in the Bundesliga, the top tier of the German football league system, The club was founded in 1899 and have won one German championship, five DFB-Pokals and one UEFA Cup. Since 1925, their stadium has been the Waldstadion, which was renamed Commerzbank-Arena in 2005.
/wiki/Hern%C3%A1n_Bernardello: Hernán Darío Bernardello (born 3 August 1986) is an Argentine footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Club Atlético Belgrano.
/wiki/UD_Almer%C3%ADa: Unión Deportiva Almería, S.A.D. (Spanish pronunciation: [uˈnjon depoɾˈtiβ(a) almeˈɾi.a]) is a Spanish football club based in Almería, in the autonomous community of Andalusia. Founded in 26 July 1989 and known as Almería Club de Fútbol until 2001, the club plays in Segunda División, and plays their homes games at Estadio de los Juegos Mediterráneos, with a 15,000-seat capacity.
/wiki/Adri%C3%A1n_L%C3%B3pez_Rodr%C3%ADg: Adrián López Rodríguez (born 25 February 1987), also known as Piscu, is a Spanish professional footballer who plays as a central defender.
Wigan Athletic Football Club (/ˈwɪɡən/) is an English professional association football club based in Wigan, Greater Manchester, England, which competes in the EFL Championship, the second tier of the English football league system, Founded in 1932, the club have played at the 25,000-seater DW Stadium since 1999, before which they played at Springfield Park. Their colours are blue and white stripes, although all-blue shirts have been common throughout the club's history. Wigan were elected to the Football League in 1978, and competed in the Premier League from 2005 to 2013.
/wiki/2013_Montreal_Impact_season: The 2013 Montreal Impact season was the club's second season Major League Soccer, the top flight of both American and Canadian soccer.
